305
00:36:47,573 --> 00:36:49,873
I wanna--
I wanna pause it.

306
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:51,541
When?

307
00:36:52,643 --> 00:36:56,246
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

308
00:36:56,248 --> 00:36:58,348
See?
Why does she do that?

309
00:36:58,350 --> 00:37:00,850
They're holding hands.
It's her dad.
And she just lets go.

310
00:37:04,689 --> 00:37:06,990
<i>[ Train Whistle Blowing ]</i>

311
00:37:08,826 --> 00:37:11,861
[ Train Whistle Blowing ]

312
00:37:46,464 --> 00:37:48,765
[ Ben ]
Did you grow up here?

313
00:37:48,767 --> 00:37:51,701
[ Angela ]
Yeah, in the summers.

314
00:37:51,703 --> 00:37:56,506
My mom and my little brother
moved here full-time
after my dad--

315
00:37:58,676 --> 00:38:03,046
Did you know
that this whole area
is a-- is a dried-up sea?

316
00:38:05,383 --> 00:38:07,050
Oh, yeah?

317
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:09,619
I did my research.

318
00:38:09,621 --> 00:38:12,455
My dad's been trying
to get me to visit
for a while.

319
00:38:15,326 --> 00:38:16,760
What do you do?

320
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:20,997
Study rocks,

321
00:38:20,999 --> 00:38:22,699
more or less.

322
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:29,939
