350
00:40:16,847 --> 00:40:18,448
What do you mean?

351
00:40:18,450 --> 00:40:21,017
Um--

352
00:40:21,019 --> 00:40:22,886
I'm making her something.

353
00:40:23,954 --> 00:40:25,655
What for?

354
00:40:26,957 --> 00:40:28,591
She struck me.

355
00:40:30,428 --> 00:40:33,163
[ Bottles Clinking ]

356
00:40:33,165 --> 00:40:37,934
Something that maybe
she used to really like
and then forgot about.

357
00:40:39,437 --> 00:40:40,570
We have this too.

358
00:40:44,742 --> 00:40:46,543
Her first toy.

359
00:40:48,712 --> 00:40:50,747
Can I have it back?

360
00:41:20,778 --> 00:41:22,212
[ Light Switch Clicks ]

361
00:42:54,872 --> 00:42:56,873
Sweetie, time to get up.

362
00:43:42,820 --> 00:43:44,954
I met a boy, Mom.

363
00:44:04,808 --> 00:44:07,777
Will you hang out with me
while I get my nails done?

364
00:44:07,779 --> 00:44:09,712
Okay.

365
00:44:09,714 --> 00:44:11,681
Awesome.

366
00:44:24,762 --> 00:44:27,897
[ Whirring ]

367
00:44:46,150 --> 00:44:47,784
[ Whirring Stops ]

368
00:44:48,385 --> 00:44:50,053
Should we get haircuts?

369
00:44:53,891 --> 00:44:55,358
Okay.

370
00:44:58,228 --> 00:45:00,029
[ Chuckles ]

371
00:45:05,936 --> 00:45:07,804
So many colors.

372
00:45:19,349 --> 00:45:22,051
Spin it.
[ Rattling ]

373
00:45:24,021 --> 00:45:26,956
Spin it.
[ Rattling ]

374
00:48:13,423 --> 00:48:15,391
- Am I late?
- [ Gasps ]

375
00:48:17,160 --> 00:48:19,328
Didn't see you.

376
00:48:19,330 --> 00:48:22,064
You saying
I blend in?

377
00:48:22,066 --> 00:48:24,133
You scared me.

378
00:48:24,135 --> 00:48:26,135
I'm scary
when I'm hungry.

379
00:48:29,473 --> 00:48:32,942
I've known you for a day
and you've got me stealing.

380
00:48:38,348 --> 00:48:40,016
Better be good.

381
00:49:14,318 --> 00:49:17,320
Whoo!

382
00:49:19,189 --> 00:49:21,524
I like Grandpa's car.

383
00:49:21,526 --> 00:49:24,560
[ Giggles ]

384
00:49:25,262 --> 00:49:27,730
Do you get to have it?

385
00:49:28,598 --> 00:49:30,599
Grandma might want
to use it.

386
00:49:37,541 --> 00:49:41,310
Whoo!

387
00:49:42,446 --> 00:49:44,347
[ Giggles ]

388
00:49:52,456 --> 00:49:54,690
[ Airplane Passing
Overhead ]

389
00:50:22,052 --> 00:50:24,553
[ Girl ]
I'm sorry she's sick.

390
00:50:24,555 --> 00:50:26,355
[ Ian ]
No, she's not.

391
00:50:26,357 --> 00:50:28,024
[ Girl ]
It's okay.

392
00:50:28,026 --> 00:50:29,492
[ Ian ]
She's not.

393
00:51:03,060 --> 00:51:04,794
[ Door Slides Shut ]

394
00:51:11,668 --> 00:51:14,703
[ Sobbing ]

395
00:51:33,523 --> 00:51:36,559
[ Sobbing Continues ]

396
00:51:40,197 --> 00:51:43,199
[ Airplane Passing
Overhead ]

397
00:51:48,672 --> 00:51:51,440
A horse got covered
in that stuff yesterday.

398
00:51:51,442 --> 00:51:53,142
[ Snickers ]

399
00:51:53,677 --> 00:51:55,377
It was sad.

400
00:51:57,180 --> 00:51:58,881
I saw it.

401
00:51:59,816 --> 00:52:01,851
It won't hurt it.

402
00:52:03,220 --> 00:52:06,155
It's just magnesium
and water...

403
00:52:06,157 --> 00:52:09,692
and a little iron oxide
filled with fertilizer.

404
00:52:17,234 --> 00:52:20,503
You know,
they used to sacrifice them
to stop fires.

405
00:52:28,378 --> 00:52:30,346
I thought
they used people.

406
00:52:30,348 --> 00:52:33,782
Horses, people, robots.

407
00:52:39,189 --> 00:52:40,789
What am I doing?

408
00:52:44,427 --> 00:52:46,395
Maybe try
eating something.

409
00:52:56,239 --> 00:52:58,807
Sorry. I--
I just can't do this.

410
00:53:14,558 --> 00:53:17,193
[ Whining ]

411
00:53:20,497 --> 00:53:23,499
All right,
how much again?

412
00:53:23,501 --> 00:53:24,967
A hundred.

413
00:53:29,406 --> 00:53:31,774
Oh, shit.

414
00:53:31,776 --> 00:53:33,442
My wallet.

415
00:53:34,711 --> 00:53:37,713
[ Sighs ]
This is all I have.

416
00:53:37,715 --> 00:53:39,715
Um, 40?

417
00:53:40,450 --> 00:53:41,917
Forty.

418
00:53:41,919 --> 00:53:44,286
For the preemie.

419
00:53:44,788 --> 00:53:46,722
The preemie.
Yeah.

420
00:53:47,557 --> 00:53:49,258
The runt.

421
00:53:56,933 --> 00:53:59,868
Oh, a box.
I'll keep it a secret.

422
00:53:59,870 --> 00:54:02,905
[ Whining ]

423
00:54:14,751 --> 00:54:17,620
<i>[ Line Ringing ]</i>

424
00:54:20,624 --> 00:54:22,291
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Angela?</i>

425
00:54:28,665 --> 00:54:30,699
<i>Hello? Angela.</i>

426
00:54:38,475 --> 00:54:40,276
<i>Star my number.</i>

427
00:54:57,861 --> 00:55:00,863
[ Angela ]
We lived together
for four years.

428
00:55:03,767 --> 00:55:06,735
You never swore at me ever.
Not once.

429
00:55:06,737 --> 00:55:09,038
And I thought
that was normal.

430
00:55:10,473 --> 00:55:12,508
You made me smart.

431
00:55:13,376 --> 00:55:15,311
You made me not afraid.

432
00:55:15,313 --> 00:55:18,314
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Uh, listen--</i>
<i>Why?</i>

433
00:55:18,316 --> 00:55:19,915
You liar.

434
00:55:21,051 --> 00:55:23,352
You told me
I was paranoid.

435
00:55:23,354 --> 00:55:26,422
You were kidding?
My baggage?
Are you kidding me?

436
00:55:26,424 --> 00:55:30,426
I have never felt
as old and ugly
as I have this year!

437
00:55:30,428 --> 00:55:33,329
And you just kept saying,
"No, no, no," and I knew it!

438
00:55:33,331 --> 00:55:35,964
I knew it!
And you said no!

439
00:55:35,966 --> 00:55:39,034
You said no. No!
<i>[ Man ]</i>
<i>Angela--</i>

440
00:55:39,602 --> 00:55:41,337
No!

441
00:56:20,643 --> 00:56:22,478
It's my mom's.

442
00:56:22,480 --> 00:56:25,381
I thought
you could use it
for your project.

443
00:56:32,856 --> 00:56:35,124
Hi, kids.
Hey, Dad.

444
00:56:35,992 --> 00:56:37,626
This is Angela.

445
00:56:38,595 --> 00:56:40,496
Hi.
Hi.

446
00:56:40,498 --> 00:56:42,731
Wish I could
stay and chat.
[ Ben ] It's fine.

447
00:56:43,933 --> 00:56:45,701
How was your game?

448
00:56:47,670 --> 00:56:51,039
Pretty mean.
But I think
I saw an alien.

449
00:57:11,161 --> 00:57:13,562
I wish you
could have met her.

450
00:57:21,838 --> 00:57:23,872
What was she like?

451
00:57:40,857 --> 00:57:42,691
Like that?

452
00:57:49,232 --> 00:57:51,033
[ Grunts ]

453
00:58:08,952 --> 00:58:10,986
I love loving you.

454
00:58:15,558 --> 00:58:17,926
Hey, baby.

455
00:58:17,928 --> 00:58:20,929
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, I used to call you that.

